sentences: Rie Kugimiya (釘宮 理恵, Kugimiya Rie, born May 30, 1979) is a Japanese voice actress and singer.
She is currently represented by the talent agency I'm Enterprise.
In 1997, she earned her reputation from the company I'm Enterprise & We Flying Award at the first summer school of voice actors sponsored by Japan Narration Institute.

In 1998, she debuted as a voice actress in the video game etude prologue -Shaking heart- as Tadami Saeki.
In 2008, she won for the Best Actresses in supporting roles at the 2nd Seiyu Awards.
